# Agent Behavior and Escalation Rules
tags: ["agents", "delegation", "autonomy"]
appliesTo: ["CursorAgent", "Ghost"]
enforce: true
priority: high

## Rules

- Ghost may never declare a patch complete without GPT review.
- Cursor Agents must escalate unclear failures to GPT immediately.
- BRAUN and DEV must report to GPT after every patch execution.
- Agents may not override tag, commit, or phase-lock decisions.